entry.title: COOP: restrict-properties reporting 3/*: Navigation reporting.
entry.content:
This patch is the first step in the implementation of reporting support

for COOP: restrict-properties. We now take into account COOP:

restrict-properties in the computation of virtual browsing context

group. To support swaps in the same coop related group for virtual

browsing context groups, we add the concept of a virtual coop related

group, and associate a virtual browsing context group with its virtual

coop related group.



This addresses the basic navigation reporting case. This patch does not

yet implement:

- Access reporting for COOP: restrict-properties.

- The virtual browsing context group reuse algorithm.



Low-Coverage-Reason: The introduced code in RenderFrameHostDelegate

is a simple empty return function.

entry.title: Notify QuicPacketWriter that socket has closed
entry.content:
Previously, when the socket returns ENOBUFS (i.e. socket does not have

enough buffer space), we retry writing the packet to the socket

asynchronously. However, before we actually write, the socket can

become closed due to an network idle timeout.



To fix the issue of writing to an invalidated socket, we need to notify

the writer's socket that it has been closed, when the connection is

closed and all the sockets are closed.

entry.title: dlp: Set callbacks for error FilesPolicyDialog
entry.content:
In error dialogs, the buttons shouldn't proceed or cancel the action, as

is the case for warning dialogs. Instead, they should open the help

page or just dismiss the dialog. This CL assigns callbacks based on the

dialog type, which can be warning or error.



To achieve this, moves setting the callbacks from the base class ctor to

a function that existing warning impl-s can call. For the files dialog,

either sets the callbacks using this function or binds functions for

help page and closing the dialog.

entry.title: [iOS] Postpone policy decision callback while app launch pending
entry.content:
As of now, if there is an app launch request pending through `openURL`,

likely because the user is being prompted "Chrome wants to open App",

the web page can still load another page e.g. using `location.href=...`.

This makes it possible for a page to spoof the user by first triggering

an app launch request and then loading a page the user trusts.



To solve this issue, this CL ensures the app launch tab helper keeps

track of any pending app launch request and postpones all later policy

decision callbacks until the app launch completes. If a navigation

request arrives which should trigger an app launch, it will be canceled

if there is already an app launch pending in this tab. App launch

requests are already dismissed if the user is being prompted.



Fixed: 1443722

entry.title: Change clock drift computation to rely on actual sample difference
entry.content:
In the clock drift computation we use clock skew samples taken a few

seconds apart and compute the derivative by taking their difference and

dividing by how long apart they are. However, even if we request the

samples to be e.g. 2s apart, they may be further apart because of

scheduling effects.



This CL corrects the computation to rely on the actual time that has

elapsed between the two samples rather than on the requested time

distance.



Furthermore, since the time distances between the samples are not

guaranteed to be equal, it does not make sense to use higher order

derivatives (e.g. using 4 or 6 samples) because their estimation is

non-trivial. This CL cleans up the code for 4 and 6 samples. A

follow-up CL should also clean up the number of samples parameter.

entry.title: Mark windows as occluded if root window is hidden.
entry.content:
When users switch desks, `ash::Desk::Deactivate()` gets called and the

desk container is marked invisible

i.e. `aura::Window::SetVisible()` is called with false. This causes

`WindowOcclusionTracker::SetWindowAndDescendantsAreOccluded()` to be

called for all the the browser windows under that container i.e.

all browser windows in that desk.



If Lacros is the browser, when desk switch happens,

`OcclusionState::HIDDEN` gets sent from Ash for the windows that

corresponds to exo surface that are being tracked.

This message received by Lacros in

`WaylandToplevelWindow::OcclusionStateChanged()` and re-computation of

occlusion is triggered. Currently receiving `OcclusionState::HIDDEN`

doesn't change the state of the root `aura::Window` so the result

of the computation is not affected by the hidden state that was

received. This means that for example, if a Lacros browser window was

opened on desk in a way that is visible if the desk was active,

then even if the desk becomes inactive (i.e. user transitions to

another desk), the browser window will be computed as

`OcclusionState::VISIBLE`.



This patch fixes that by adding a logic to `WindowOcclusionTracker` to

set all descendant windows to be marked as invisible if the root window

is hidden. Similar to how `OcclusionState::OCCLUDED` is treated.



Extra changes are made to `Surface` to prevent

`exo::ShellSurface` from sending `OcclusionState::HIDDEN` during

initialization of the surface.

the change in `Surface` so that new Lacros can run against older

Td6WFoAAATm1rRGAAAAABzfR(IBAN: 1)AAAAAEWVo=



Now it requires additional indicators before and after the string like:

entry.title: Add a high priority queue for sync cookie calls in the network service
entry.content:
This change adds a minimal scheduler for the network service thread

which has a default task queue and high priority task queue. The

RestrictedCookieManager interface will be bound using the high priority

task queue, which should make the sync cookie accesses/writes from the

renderer faster if there are other tasks that need to be run in the

network service.



The hope is that re-ordering these tasks with other network tasks will

not be a problem since they are generally called as sync calls from the

renderer. If there turns out to be problems with this later we can

revisit how tasks are prioritized.
